oc:kn_1b68b3a3 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When implementing waitFor/polling functions" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Always include a timeout with a clear error message in waitFor loops. Never loop forever." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Without a timeout, a condition that is never met causes tests to hang indefinitely, hiding the real failure" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_4b739f85 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:RecoveryTactic ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When condition checks seem to return outdated values" ;
    oc:directiveContent "If stale data is suspected, call the getter inside the loop for fresh data rather than caching state before the loop." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Caching before the loop captures a snapshot that never updates, causing the condition to never be satisfied" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_564172b3 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:KnownIssue ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When implementing polling loops" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Polling too fast (setTimeout(check, 1)) wastes CPU. Use 10ms as the polling interval." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Sub-millisecond polling creates unnecessary CPU load without meaningful improvement in responsiveness" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_7643be75 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing or fixing tests that depend on async operations" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never use arbitrary delays (setTimeout, sleep, time.sleep()) to guess at async timing in tests." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Arbitrary delays create race conditions — tests pass on fast machines but fail under load or in CI" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_864fe9a2 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PerformanceProfile ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Always" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Condition-based waiting is faster than fixed delays because it proceeds immediately when the condition is met rather than waiting the full delay period." ;
    oc:hasRationale "A 5s timeout with 10ms polling will return in ~10ms if the condition is already met, versus waiting the full fixed delay" .

oc:kn_8ec53bb1 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When a fixed delay is genuinely necessary" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Arbitrary timeouts are acceptable ONLY when testing actual timing behavior (debounce, throttle), and must be: (1) preceded by a condition-based wait, (2) based on known timing, and (3) documented with a comment explaining WHY." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Some behaviors are inherently time-based; the documentation ensures future maintainers understand the delay is intentional and justified" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_f3283b60 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Always, when any test waiting is needed" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Wait for the actual condition you care about, not a guess about how long it takes." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Condition-based waiting is deterministic and faster than fixed delays because it proceeds as soon as the condition is met" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_f47718ec a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:SuccessIndicator ;
    oc:appliesToContext "After applying condition-based waiting to flaky tests" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Test pass rate reaches 100% and execution time improves measurably (observed: 60%→100% pass rate, 40% faster execution)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Measurable improvement in reliability and speed confirms the pattern was correctly applied" .

